Location: Wooden art Lir Sculputure  No 1 Coast Road R106
Description: Wooden sculpture by the Limerick based artist Simon Donnelly.   Created from blown down trees  blown down in new street malahide.   Originally intended to be returned to New Street they have instead been put into Green areas around Malahide.   Simon based his ideas around local poetry, Malahide’s proximity to the sea and the biodiversity in Malahide Demesne.
